# Generate Slides

## Goal
Render content from the {{config.project.name}} wiki into a Marp-formatted slide deck.

**The wiki is canonical; the slide deck is a view.** Read from `wiki/`, write to `outputs/slides/`. Never modify wiki pages.

<workflow>

<step n="1" goal="Determine slide deck parameters">
  <action>Ask the user for: topic/scope, target audience, desired number of slides, presentation style (overview, deep-dive, comparison)</action>
  <check if="user did not specify scope">
    <action>Suggest a scope based on `wiki/overview.md` key themes</action>
  </check>
</step>

<step n="2" goal="Apply lifecycle filter to wiki sources">
  <action>Before reading pages from the wiki, exclude any page whose frontmatter has `status: superseded` or `status: archived` — those are historical record by definition, not current claims.</action>
  <action>Proceed only with pages marked `status: current` (or pages with no `status` field set, which lint treats as `current` by default).</action>
  <check if="this deliverable specifically requires historical context (e.g., a before/after comparison or a retrospective)">
    <action>Include superseded pages explicitly, and annotate every claim drawn from them — in tables, italicize the row and add "(historical)"; in prose, footnote-link to the superseding page using {{config.wiki.cross_ref_style}}.</action>
  </check>
  <check if="any included page has `last_verified` older than {{config.maturity.decay_threshold_days}} days">
    <action>Annotate that claim with a "verification age" marker in the output (e.g., "last verified {N} days ago") so the reader can judge freshness without leaving the document.</action>
  </check>
</step>

<step n="3" goal="Gather content from wiki">
  <action>Identify relevant wiki pages based on the specified scope</action>
  <action>Read each page and extract key points suitable for slides</action>
  <action>Prioritize high-confidence claims and well-sourced information</action>
</step>

<step n="4" goal="Create slide outline">
  <action>Draft a slide-by-slide outline: title slide, agenda, content slides, summary, references</action>
  <action>Each content slide: title, 3-5 bullet points, optional speaker notes</action>
{{#if (eq config.workflows.ingestion_style "autonomous")}}
  <action>Proceed with the draft outline — log it with `[AUTO] slides-outline | proceeding with {slide count} slides`</action>
{{else}}
  <action>Present outline to user for approval</action>
{{/if}}
</step>

<step n="5" goal="Write Marp-formatted slides">
  <action>Write the slide deck in Marp markdown format:</action>
  <action>Use `---` to separate slides</action>
  <action>Use `marp: true` in YAML frontmatter</action>
  <action>Keep slides concise: title + 3-5 bullets maximum per slide</action>
  <action>Add speaker notes with {{config.wiki.cross_ref_style}} citations to wiki pages</action>
</step>

<step n="6" goal="Save and report">
  <action>Save to `outputs/slides/{topic-slug}.md`</action>
  <action>Log the slide generation in `wiki/log.md`</action>
  <action>Report: number of slides, wiki pages referenced, any content gaps noted</action>
</step>

</workflow>
